New Records: Ireland recorded their first win in the Super 12 stage of a T20 World Cup.
Key Match Events: Ireland won by five runs in a rain-affected match.
Alex Hales, Jos Buttler, and Ben Stokes fell without scoring much in the first four overs.
Moeen Ali attempted a fightback but it was not enough.
Dawid Malan top-edged a pull and was caught, leaving England at 86/5 in 13.1 overs.
Harry Brook was caught by Delaney off Dockrell, leaving England at 67/4 in 10.5 overs.
Post-Match Reflections: Ireland's players celebrated with their fans after the win.
The result throws Group 1 wide open with five of the six teams now on two points.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted play in the 15th over, leading to the application of the DLS method.
England were behind the par score of 110 when the rain came.
